        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Soften the base",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Melt {{unsalted-butter}} of butter in a large saucepan over a medium-low heat. Add the {{onion}} onion and {{leek}} leek with a pinch of salt. Cook for 8 minutes until soft.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the {{garlic}} of crushed garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Cook the broccoli",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the {{potato}} of potato chunks and {{broccoli}} broccoli. Pour over {{stock-vegetable}} of hot vegetable stock. Bring to a simmer, cover, and cook for 15 minutes until everything is tender.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Blend and add the Stilton",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Remove from the heat. Blend with a stick blender until smooth.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Return the pan to a low heat. Add {{stilton}} of crumbled ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Stilton",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "termId": "cmpry046y0000d8v4jykw37y1"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " and stir until melted in. Add {{double-cream}} of cream if using. Taste: you may not need additional salt as the cheese is already salty.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Ladle into bowls. Crumble a little extra Stilton over each portion and add a twist of black pepper.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Keep the cooking time to 15 minutes maximum. The broccoli should be tender, not mushy. Longer cooking destroys the chlorophyll and turns the colour dull.",
                "cause": "The broccoli was overcooked.",
                "symptom": "Soup turns grey-green rather than bright green"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Start with 80 g, blend, taste, and add more to your preference. The amount in this recipe suits a standard young Stilton; reduce if using a particularly strong piece.",
                "cause": "The quantity was too high for the mild broccoli base, or the Stilton was very aged and sharp.",
                "symptom": "Stilton is too dominant"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Use the broccoli stem as well as the florets. The stem blends more smoothly than the florets alone. Make sure the potato is completely soft before blending.",
                "cause": "Not enough potato to give body, or the broccoli stems were too coarse.",
                "symptom": "Soup is grainy after blending"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Take the pan off the heat before stirring in the Stilton. Stir steadily rather than whisking, and keep the heat very low when you return it to warm through.",
                "cause": "The soup was too hot when the cheese was added, causing the fat to separate.",
                "symptom": "Soup splits or looks curdled after the Stilton is added"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Broccoli and Stilton soup belongs to the tradition of using strong British cheese to carry a mild vegetable base, in the same way that cauliflower cheese uses a béchamel. Stilton is one of England's great protected cheeses, made in three Midlands counties, and this soup is one of the most efficient ways to use it. It appears on pub lunch menus across the country, usually in a brown bread roll that costs half as much again.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "servings": 4,
